<aura:documentation>
	<aura:description>
    <div class="slds-m-top_large">
    <h4>Overview</h4>    
    <p>The <code>&lt;c:PEG_ActionGroup_CMP&gt;</code> is a utility component enabling
        to display a group of actions (as buttons or menus) and trigger a callback
        method when one of them is clicked.</p>
    <p>It is typically used in the <code>&lt;c:PEG_ActionGroupDisplay_CMP&gt;</code>
        component to be instantiated within Lightning pages via the App Builder or
        the <code>&lt;c:PEG_SoqlList_CMP&gt;</code> component to add header actions
        to a list table.</p>
    <br/>
    </div>
        
    <div class="slds-m-top_large">
    <h4>Usage</h4>
    <p>Basically, two elements should be provided when instantiating the
        <code>&lt;c:PEG_ActionGroup_CMP&gt;</code> in another one:</p>
    <ul>
    <li><code>actionList</code> with the JSON array of actions to be displayed.</li>
    <li><code>callback</code> with a javascript handler method.</li>
    </ul>
<pre>&lt;c:PEG_ActionGroup_CMP actionList='{!v.actionListJson}'
                       callback='{!c.handleAction}' /&gt;</pre>
    <p>In the action handler, the JSON object corresponding to the action triggered
        as-is as the message of the callback parameters.</p>
    <br/>
    </div>
        
